  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense in most countries. It typically falls under criminal legislation and is prosecuted as a serious financial crime. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations that criminalize such activities, with potential penalties including significant fines and imprisonment.",
